  "description": {
    "en": "Equipped with thick white coats and special hooves, they easily navigate extreme alpine environments.",
    "zh": "配备厚厚的白色皮毛和特殊的蹄子，它们能轻松在极端高山环境中穿梭。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "Mountain goats stand about 1 meter tall at the shoulder and weigh 45 to 140 kilograms, with males being larger than females. They are covered in thick, woolly white fur that keeps them warm in freezing temperatures. Their hooves have hard outer edges and soft, rubbery pads underneath that grip rocky surfaces like climbing shoes.",
      "zh": "雪羊肩高约1米，体重45到140公斤，雄性比雌性更大。它们全身覆盖着厚厚的白色羊毛，能在冰冻的温度中保暖。它们的蹄子外缘坚硬，底部有柔软的橡胶状肉垫，能像攀岩鞋一样抓住岩石表面。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "Mountain goats eat grasses, mosses, lichens, and other alpine plants. They are incredible climbers that can scale nearly vertical cliff faces to escape predators like eagles and mountain lions. In spring, they travel to natural salt licks to get important minerals their bodies need.",
      "zh": "雪羊吃草、苔藓、地衣和其他高山植物。它们是令人难以置信的攀爬高手，能攀上几乎垂直的悬崖来躲避鹰和美洲狮等捕食者。春天，它们会去天然盐碱地舔食身体所需的重要矿物质。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Mountain goats live high up in the steep, rocky mountains of western North America, usually above the tree line. They are found from southeastern Alaska through British Columbia and into the northern Rocky Mountains of the United States. They prefer the most rugged, inaccessible peaks where few other animals can survive.",
      "zh": "雪羊生活在北美洲西部陡峭的岩石山峰高处，通常在树线以上。它们分布从阿拉斯加东南部到不列颠哥伦比亚省，再到美国北部落基山脉。它们偏爱最崎岖、最难以到达的山峰，那里很少有其他动物能够生存。"
    }
  },
